# Critical Technical & Product Review: The Bandit v0 Design (Three-Doc System)

## TL;DR
- **The central "measurable workflow improvement loop" thesis is the single weakest part of Bandit and likely a category error.** The literature is unambiguous that engineering-process measurement is hostile to causal attribution, and the most recent rigorous RCT (METR, 2025, 16 devs / 246 tasks) found AI tools *slowed* experienced developers by 19% while they self-reported a 20% speedup — exactly the wrong direction for a self-improvement loop driven by operator-visible metrics. At Bandit's single-operator volume, keep/revise/revert/double-down decisions on "workflow changes" are statistically indefensible; this is cargo-cult metrics dressed as a learning system, and the system can plausibly reward-hack itself into worse behavior.
- **Auto-landing under a non-coder operator with "cooperative-only" security is the most dangerous concrete design choice.** An October 2025 disclosure publicly detailed in April 2026 (Aonan Guan with Johns Hopkins collaborators) showed Anthropic's Claude Code Security Review, Google's Gemini CLI Action, and GitHub's Copilot Coding Agent all leaked secrets via a single prompt-injected PR title — Anthropic initially rated it CVSS 9.4 Critical. Bandit's Landing Agent + a non-coder who is *defined* as unable to sanity-check warnings is precisely the configuration this attack class targets. The "smell list" and stacked reviewers do not address it.
- **The non-product surface — JSONL-as-canonical, 10-role decomposition, CLI-authority, local-Qwen-as-baseline-reviewer — ranges from defensible (CLI authority, JSONL events) to fragile (no event schema versioning, Qwen as a *security-grade* adversarial reviewer) to over-decomposed (10 roles for a single-operator system). None of these is a fatal flaw individually; collectively they create a system whose complexity exceeds the evidence base supporting its central claims.

**Aggregate verdict, by area:** Measurable improvement loop — **ILL-ADVISED as currently framed**. Cross-model review with local Qwen baseline — **RISKY**. Auto-landing for non-coder — **ILL-ADVISED**. Smell-based escalation list — **RISKY**. JSONL canonical state — **SOUND with caveats**. CLI authority + thin UI — **SOUND**. Attention-first IA — **SOUND**. 10-role taxonomy — **RISKY (over-decomposed)**. Missing surface (agent evals, prompt-injection posture, supply chain) — **ILL-ADVISED to omit**.

